# Rootbox

[![image](https://img.shields.io/pypi/v/rootbox.svg)](https://pypi.python.org/pypi/rootbox)
[![image](https://img.shields.io/pypi/pyversions/rootbox.svg)](https://pypi.python.org/pypi/rootbox)
![License](https://img.shields.io/github/license/joaompinto/rootbox?style=flat-square)
[![Code style: black](https://img.shields.io/badge/code%20style-black-000000.svg?style=flat-square)](https://github.com/ambv/black)
[![Actions status](https://github.com/joaompinto/rootbox/actions/workflows/ci.yaml/badge.svg
)](https://github.com/joaompinto/rootbox/actions)

An extremely simple and fast container engine for Linux and WSL, written in Python.

- üåé Installable/usable by any user, does not require root privileges
- ‚ö°Ô∏è Faster due to the use of in-memory filesystems and minimal set of features
- üêç Simple code base written in Python, simple to understand and extend
- üõ†Ô∏è Development library for embedding container support in other applications
- ü§ù Python 3.11 compatibility
- üì¶ Uses regular remote or local tarball for images, no need for a registry
- üêß [LXC Containers Images](https://images.linuxcontainers.org/) support
- üìñ [Documentation](https://rootbox.pages.dev/)
